In April this year, a ‘shari’a’ court found the man “guilty of obtaining an abortion while knowing this action to be forbidden in Islam” and sentenced him to two years in jail, even though “the prosecution failed to prove he had precise knowledge that his testimony would lead to the abortion being performed or procured…” Two months later, the man was sentenced to 80 lashes because he was convicted of “adultery”.
